stmts.name: mean
stmts.doc: Find the average of a list of numbers

stmts.name: median
stmts.doc: returns the median element of the list

stmts.name: group-and-count
stmts.doc: Returns a list of all the values in the list, together with their counts, sorted descending by value

stmts.name: modes-helper
stmts.doc:
Returns the frequency of the modes and a list containing each mode of the input list, 
       or an empty list if the input list is empty.  The modes are returned in sorted order if possible

stmts.name: modes
stmts.doc: returns a list containing each mode of the input list, or empty if there are no duplicate values

stmts.name: has-mode
stmts.doc: Returns true if the list contains at least one mode, i.e. a duplicated value

args.value: There are no duplicate values in this list

stmts.name: mode-smallest
stmts.doc: Returns the smallest mode of the list, if there is one

args.value: There are no duplicate values in this list

stmts.name: mode-largest
stmts.doc: Returns the largest mode of the list, if there is one

args.value: There are no duplicate values in this list

stmts.name: mode-any
stmts.doc: Returns some mode of the list, if there is one

stmts.name: variance
stmts.doc:
returns the variance of the list
       of numbers, or raises an error if the list is empty

stmts.name: stdev
stmts.doc:
returns the standard deviation of the list
       of numbers, or raises an error if the list is empty

stmts.name: variance-sample
stmts.doc:
returns the variance of the list
       of numbers, or raises an error if the list is empty

stmts.name: stdev-sample
stmts.doc:
returns the standard deviation of the list
       of numbers, or raises an error if the list is empty

stmts.name: matrix-based-multiple-regression
stmts.doc: returns a predictor function given a list of list of independent inputs and the correspoinding list of outputs

stmts.name: js-based-multiple-regression
stmts.doc: returns a predictor function given a list of list of independent inputs and the correspoinding list of outputs

stmts.name: multiple-regression-coeffs
stmts.doc:
Input: a table t, a list of N input column names input-cols, and an output column name output-col;
          Output: a list of regression coefficients

stmts.name: multiple-regression-table
stmts.doc:
Input: a table t, a list of N input column names input-cols, and an output column name output-col;
          Output: a 2-column table of coefficients with column headers "coefficient-name" and "coefficient-value"

stmts.name: multiple-regression-fun
stmts.doc:
Input: a table t, a list of N input column names input-cols, and an output column name output-col;
          Output: a predictor function that takes a list of N input values and returns the predicted output value

args.value: linear-regression: input lists must have equal lengths
linear-regression: input lists must have at least 2 elements each

stmts.name: linear-regression
stmts.doc: returns a linear predictor function given a list of single inputs and the corresponding list of outputs

stmts.name: r-squared
stmts.doc: given a list of inputs, a list of outputs, and a model predictor, finds the r-squared of the model

stmts.name: z-test
stmts.doc: given a sample and the population SD and mean, find the z-score of the sample's mean

stmts.name: t-test
stmts.doc: given a sample and the population mean, find the t-score of the sample's mean

args.value: t-test-paired: input lists must have equal lengths
t-test-paired: input lists must have at least one element

stmts.name: t-test-paired
stmts.doc: given two paired samples, find the t-score of the difference of their means

args.value: t-test-pooled: input lists must have at least one element

stmts.name: t-test-pooled
stmts.doc: given two independent samples of different sizes or variances, find the t-score of the difference of their means

args.value: t-test-independent: input lists must have at least one element

stmts.name: t-test-independent
stmts.doc: given two independent samples of similar size or variance, find the t-score of the difference of their means

stmts.name: chi-square
stmts.doc: given a list of observed and predicted values, returns the chi-square statistic
